Traineeship Description
This traineeship position reports to the R&amp;D manager of Neo Magnequench Business Unit. Neo Magnequench is the global leader in the NdFeB bonded magnet industry. He/she will work as a member of a team of materials scientists and participate R&amp;D projects on advanced NdFeB magnetic powders and their bonded magnets for broad industrial applications.

Specific Responsibilities
The trainee will be involved in:

  Conduct experiments of making rapidly quenched NdFeB magnetic powders and polymer bonded magnets.
  Operate instruments for the characterization of magnetic powders, polymers and their bonded magnets.
  Record and analyze experimental data, write research reports, and present results in the R&amp;D meeting
  Routine shared and assigned housekeeping and other laboratory tasks.

Technical Skills and Competencies Trainee will learn

  Learn various magnet processing techniques such as rapid-quenching, compounding, compression molding, and injection molding.
  Learn operations of various instruments such as scanning electron microscope, hysteresisgrapher, vibrating sample magnetometer, particle size analyzer, and thermal analysis instrument.
  Gain experience in project planning, execution and reporting.
  Develop ability in critical thinking and problem solving.

Education Qualifications Required
Bachelor's Degree in Materials Science and Enginering, Physics, or Chemistry

Eligibility Criteria

  Singapore Citizen or Permanent Resident; and
  Graduated or graduating in calendar year 2019 or 2020 from ITEs, polytechnics, universities, or other educational institutions (e.g. private universities and overseas institutions); or
  Graduated earlier from above institutions and completed National Service in 2019 or 2020.
